Configure Text Variables

To configure settings for individual text variables in your model:

* On the Model Settings page, click a text variable. The variable panel appears.
* In the Alerts tab, respond to suggestions regarding data issues for this field, such as high correlation or missing values.
* In the Performance tab, see how well your model works for each value within the selected variable.

To configure settings:

* SELECT THE METHOD TO TRANSFORM YOUR TEXT:
	+ Fuzzy Matching to resolve spelling variations
	+ Detect Sentiment to categorize unstructured data
	+ Text Clustering to bucket unclustered data by keywords
	+ Replace Missing Values to fill in missing values
* INCLUDE ONLY the values you want to include in the model. Excluded values are either omitted from analysis or merged into the Other category.
* TO APPLY FUZZY MATCHING:
	+ Fuzzy matching adds uniformity to spelling variations in variables, resulting in smarter categorizations and better predictions.
* TO DETECT SENTIMENT IN UNSTRUCTURED TEXT:
	+ Process unstructured data during model creation and categorize sentiment as positive, negative, or neutral.
* TO USE TEXT CLUSTERING TO ANALYZE UNSTRUCTURED DATA:
	+ Text clustering reduces unstructured data to its top keywords and enables you to quickly reveal hidden insights and improve decision making.
* TO IMPUTE MISSING TEXT VALUES:
	+ Enable imputation on a text variable, and Einstein Discovery automatically replaces missing values with data derived from another subset of your data.
title: Configure Text Variables in Salesforce Analytics
